Triglavian bioadaptive technology makes extensive use of engineered colonies of extremophilic bacteria, that are used to grow, harvest and adapt various resources found in Abyssal Deadspace. Artificial colonizing plasmids integrated into specialist tools used for direct adaptation of technology can be found in Triglavian caches in various stages of development. These mutaplasmids can be used to alter the characteristics of a wide variety of equipment types, depending on the strain and the bioadaptive tool with which they are integrated.

52236 - Zorya's Light Entropic Disintegrator This small Entropic Disintegrator is typically seen in use on Triglavian frigates and destroyers, which are able to handle the relatively minimal radiation and gravitational tidal forces the weapon generates as a side-effect of its operation.

Entropic Disintegrators draw on the tremendous power of the Triglavian singularity-based energy systems to convert exotic matter into a particle stream directed with locally generated entropic force. While powerful, the range of the weapon is limited by the attenuation of entropic forces, which dissipate critically beyond the optimal range. As a result this weapon has no falloff range.

The particle stream generates thermal and explosive reactions on impact, and the entropic forces resolve into a localized gravitational conduit that steadily increases the acceleration on the exotic particles. In effect, the weapon's damage potential increases to a maximum level as long as the particle stream is kept on the same target.

Requires exotic plasma charge ammo types: Baryon, Meson, and Tetryon.		 Precursor Weapon

52250 - Nergal Adapting the Collective's Damavik-class frigate design, the Nergal's basic premise is to turn the Triglavian light hull into an assault frigate that builds on the powerful capabilities of the core ship frame. The Nergal has been modified using a variety of designs but draws principally from the popular Enyo-class assault frigate, using the Triglavian energy systems and the light entropic disintegrator capacity create a fearsome attack ship.

As an assault frigate, the Nergal has improved microwarpdrive signature radius damping and can use an assault damage control for enhanced defense. This compact brawler also benefits from increased entropic disintegrator range and damage, while its Triglavian core systems give it advantages in the use of energy neutralizer and pulse weapons, as well as remote armor repairers.

"Refitting the core Damavik hull type with the Enyo's assault modifications was relatively straightforward due to the larger size of the ship's frame. We were also able to install improved drone bays and control bandwidth. A note on drones: one of our technicians improperly accessed a locked out section of the Triglavian encryption database and inadvertently activated a dormant subversion routine. Damage to the testbed was extensive. Unfortunately, no disciplinary action is necessary and next of kin have been informed according to cover protocols. The Navy R&D Board should consider notifying the CreoDron research group to take extra precautions." – excerpt from a report for the Federal Navy from Roden Shipyards Precursor Technology Research Group		 Assault Frigate

As a heavy assault cruiser, the Ikitursa can use an assault damage control for enhanced defense and benefits from increased entropic disintegrator range and damage, while its Triglavian core systems give it advantages in the use of energy neutralizer and pulse weapons, as well as remote armor repairers.

"We can confirm that Ishukone's propriety Heavy Assault Cruiser Enhancement Package can be adapted for use in conversion of the Vedmak design to a heavy assault configuration. We did attempt to improve shield systems on prototype 2 but overtuning the thermo-kinetic shielding caused a singularity instability alert and the experiment was aborted. 52254 - Draugur A modification of the Collective's Kikimora-class destroyer, the Draugur design takes the core of the Triglavian hull design and completely overhauls it to produce a potent example of the command destroyer type of vessel. 52351 - Nergal Singularity Storm SKIN (Permanent) Triglavian ships use a nanocoating technology on their external surfaces that is sufficiently similar to that used with the ships of other races to allow adaptation of commercial nanocoatings for use with them. Some configurations of the nanocoatings produce striking effects due to the interaction between the surface coating and the unusual design elements of Triglavian vessels.

One of these configurations takes a small amount of the excess radiation from the singularity energy systems of Triglavian ships and produces an electrical discharge on the surface of the ship. While eye-catching and unusual, this effect has a negligible impact on the performance characteristics of the ship.		 Permanent SKIN

52361 - World Ark (Xordazh-class) The immense World Ark is the center of operations for the local Triglavian forces in this invasion zone. The vessel appears to function as a mobile base of operations and is speculated to incorporate a Triglavian conduit gate through which additional forces can flow from Abyssal Deadspace to New Eden.

The Xordazh-class World Ark would seem to be easily the match of any vessel known to New Eden and is presumably at least as powerful and hard to destroy as the heaviest military structures. The ship has been observed deploying numerous "field effect subpylons" of a variety of types as part of its defensive network. Approach with extreme caution.		 Large Collidable Structure

86673 The Storm is a mixed payload submunition system, designed as a versatile all-in-one solution for any combat scenario. Consisting of three different miniature warheads (EMP, Titanium And Plasma), it is incredibly hard to counter completely with standard defensive systems. The downside is of course that individually, the warheads are much weaker than normal and it's rather easy to counter at least part of the damage done.

86773 An Infrastructure Hub is the cornerstone of any empire´s expansion into nullsec territory.

Once online, it allows the owner to cultivate the system it is placed in by applying one of the upgrades available. These upgrades range from simple improvements to a system´s financial infrastructure, to defensive upgrades giving the system owner significant advantages.

To begin upgrading a star system, deploy the Infrastructure Hub close to a planet and activate an Entosis Link on the IHub until your alliance has full control.

You must be a member of a valid Capsuleer alliance to deploy and/or take control of an IHub. A maximum of one IHub may be deployed in any star system. IHubs cannot be deployed in systems under non-Capsuleer Sovereignty. IHubs cannot be deployed in Wormhole space. The applications of such technology was not lost on the major players and the kids who invented it now head their own research divisions.

This allows the module to disrupt ships of any size, including ships normally immune to all forms of electronic warfare. 536463 This rare isotope of the mineral Isogen naturally forms stable bipyramidal crystals in the absence of the tremendous forces that typically form the more common crystal forms of Isogen, such as found in asteroids or moons. Crystalline Isogen-10 can form in space under the correct local conditions, typically requiring the in abnormal gravitation fields that are found in unusual configurations of space-time topology like Abyssal Deadspace.

Isogen-10 has been determined to be useful in the construction of light but strong materials suited to varying gravitational forces and associated accelerations. It is possible this form of Isogen could be broken down into other isotopes but they would likely be unstable, and such processes would run the risk of unleashing large quantities of energy.		 This rare isotope of the mineral Isogen naturally forms stable bipyramidal crystals in the absence of the tremendous forces that typically form the more common crystal forms of Isogen, such as found in asteroids or moons. Crystalline Isogen-10 can form in space under the correct local conditions, typically requiring the abnormal gravitation fields that are found in unusual configurations of space-time topology like Abyssal Deadspace.

Isogen-10 has been determined to be useful in the construction of light but strong materials suited to varying gravitational forces and associated accelerations. 537223 This small Entropic Disintegrator is typically seen in use on Damavik-class frigates, which are able to handle the relatively minimal radiation and gravitational tidal forces the weapon generates as a side-effect of its operation.

Entropic Disintegrators draw on the tremendous power of the Triglavian singularity-based energy systems to convert exotic matter into a particle stream directed with locally generated entropic force. While powerful, the range of the weapon is limited by the attenuation of entropic forces, which dissipate critically beyond the optimal range. As a result this weapon has no falloff range.

The particle stream generates thermal and explosive reactions on impact, and the entropic forces resolve into a localized gravitational conduit that steadily increases the acceleration on the exotic particles. In effect, the weapon's damage potential increases to a maximum level as long as the particle stream is kept on the same target.

Requires exotic plasma charge ammo types: Baryon, Meson, and Tetryon. In effect, the weapon's damage potential increases to a maximum level as long as the particle stream is kept on the same target.

Requires exotic plasma charge ammo types: Baryon, Meson, and Tetryon.		 This large Entropic Disintegrator is only seen in use on Triglavian battleships, these massive ships being capable of managing the considerable radiation and enormous gravitational tidal forces the weapon generates. At the energy levels of this superheavy weapon system, the tidal forces are such that special systems are built into the ship to counteract them.

543544 A light, long-range combat ship that may be considered the Collective's approach to standoff destroyer designs, the Kikimora is another Triglavian design that has proven adaptable to capsuleer technology, as with previously recovered examples of ship architecture recovered from Abyssal Deadspace.

As with other light combat vessels in the Triglavian lineup, the Kikimora is capable of mounting Light Entropic Disintegrators and an array of support weapons such as energy neutralizers and pulse weapons. The ship also makes limited use of drones and has a long-range remote repair capability.

543547 The first modification of Triglavian ship design using the methods of Tech II invention and construction, the Zarmazd builds on the Collective's Rodiva-class support cruiser to create a logistics cruiser adapted for capsuleer use. The Zarmazd's design combines elements of the Amarr Guardian-class armor logistics cruiser's technology with the Triglavian ship frame, energy system and signature adaptive mutaplasmid repair system.

The Zarmazd's remote repair systems are considerably enhanced by adaptive armor-repair mutaplasmids that are used as nanite feedstock for its remote repair projectors. As the armor-repair mutaplasmid stream is able to adapt itself in real-time to specific target ship conditions far more efficiently than standard armor-repair nanites, the efficiency of armor repairing performed by the nanite stream on a given target increases over time towards a maximal repair output.

"It proved possible to adapt the ship specifications provided to incorporate some of the improvements found in our own advanced logistics cruisers. The Guardian's high-output nanofabbers were readily altered to support the production of armor-repair mutaplasmids and, while the engineering challenges were novel, the increased flow and unusual nanotopography were ultimately incorporated without great difficulty. It should be noted that any competent nanotech engineer could reproduce these adaptations using the Rodiva's specifications as a basis." – excerpt from a report from the Office of the Fabricator-General of the Imperial Navy		 The first modification of Triglavian ship design using the methods of Tech II invention and construction, the Zarmazd builds on the Collective's Rodiva-class support cruiser to create a logistics cruiser adapted for capsuleer use. 548702 The war headquarters is an Upwell Structure located somewhere in highsec space owned by the attacking side of an aggressive war. The attackers choose which of their structures to designate as the war headquarters for any given war during their initial war declaration. If the war headquarters structure is destroyed by anyone or removed from space for any reason the war will enter a 24 hour cooldown and then end. If a war ends due to the destruction or removal of the war headquarters, the former attacking organization will be unable to declare new wars against the former defending organization for two weeks. 548885 Third party corporations and alliances can offer to become official allies to the defending side of a war. Ally negotiation can include a potential ISK payment from the defender to the ally to compensate them for their assistance. If this offer is accepted, the ally becomes a part of the war and will be able to shoot the attackers in the war. Allies can shoot the attacking side of a war but they are still considered third parties for the purposes of providing remote repair or remote assistance to the defending organization or other allies. Ally agreements last for two weeks or until the war ends, whichever comes first. Third party corporations and alliances can offer to become official allies to the defending side of a war. 549419 In a declared war, members of each organization may freely attack members of the opposing organization without penalty. Wars contain a 24 hour warning period before they begin so that both sides may prepare for the conflict, and when wars end they enter a 24 hour cooldown during which shooting may legally continue so that both sides can prepare for peace.
Aggressive wars are formally declared by one attacking organization against one defending organization, while mutual wars are agreed upon by both sides equally.

Aggressive wars can end if a surrender offer is accepted, if the attacking side fails to pay their weekly war bill, if the defending side loses their last structure in space, or if the attacker loses their war headquarters structure.
Wars will be inherited whenever corporations leave an alliance that is at war, or when a defending corporation joins an alliance. These inherited wars have all the same requirements as other wars, and if they do not meet any of the requirements (including war eligibility) they will enter the 24 hour cooldown and then end.

Corporations and alliances are eligible to participate in aggressive wars if they control at least one structure in space. If a corporation or alliance wishes to avoid having wars declared against them, they can choose not to deploy a structure in space.
Aggressive wars require a recurring ISK payment by the attacking side and the attacking organization must designate an Upwell Structure they control in high security space as the war headquarters for any given war.
Mutual wars do not require ISK payments or structures, can only be started by mutual agreement of both sides, and can be ended by either side at any time with 24 hours warning. 549420 ISK fees for aggressive wars must be paid by the attacking organization in order to continue the war. The initial war declaration cost represents the pre-payment for the first week of the war, and the attacking side will then receive a bill for the second week of the war that they can pay anytime before the beginning of that second week.

War bills will appear in the bills payable section of the corporation wallet approximately one week before they are due, and can be paid manually or set to auto-pay as desired.
If war bills are not paid on time, the war will enter a 24 cooldown period and then end.

Mutual wars do not require ISK payments.		 ISK fees for aggressive wars must be paid by the attacking organization in order to continue the war. 549421 The defenders in a war may choose to seek assistance in the war and open itself for ally offers. Potential allies can then offer their services to the defenders either for free or for an ISK fee. If an ally offer is accepted, there will be a 4 hour warning period after which the ally organization will enter a state of war with the attacking organization for two weeks.

Potential ally corporations or alliances will need to be war eligible at the start of their ally period, although losing their structures will not eject them from the ally state early.
The first active ally in any given war does not have any CONCORD ISK fees above and beyond the fee requested by the ally. The second active ally requires a CONCORD fee of 10 million ISK above and beyond the ISK fee requested by the ally, and this CONCORD fee doubles for each additional ally beyond the second.

Allies are not available for the attacking side of a war, or for either side of a mutual war.

Although allies are able to assist the defenders by shooting and otherwise disrupting the attackers, allies will be subject to the normal third party penalties if they use remote assistance modules to repair or boost members of the defending organization or other allies. UI/Corporations/Wars/LandingPageAlliesTooltip
549422 Mutual wars are started through an invite/acceptance system, which requires consent from both sides. Mutual wars allow the same free and unimpeded combat between the two organizations in empire space as aggressive wars, without the war eligibility, war headquarters, or ISK fee requirements of an aggressive war.

Mutual wars may be ended by either party at will, with the standard 24 hour cooldown before combat stops.

Allies are not available in mutual wars.		 Mutual wars are started through an invite/acceptance system, which requires consent from both sides. 549423 Corporations and alliances must be war eligible to participate in aggressive wars as an attacker, defender, or to begin their period as an ally. If the last structure owned by a corporation or alliance leaves space or is destroyed, any aggressive wars in which they are the attacker or defender will enter a 24 hour cooldown and then end.

The following types of player-owned structures count towards war eligibility: All Upwell Structures (including Upwell FLEX structures), starbase control towers, customs offices and customs office gantries, infrastructure hubs and territorial control units.
Structures in any area of space count towards war eligibility.
If any member corporation of an alliance owns at least one structure in space, the whole alliance becomes war eligible.

Attackers must designate a specific Upwell Structure that they own in highsec space as their war headquarters for a given aggressive war. If this war headquarters structure is destroyed or removed from space for any reason during the war, the war will enter a 24 hour cooldown and then end. If a war ends due to the removal of the war headquarters, the former attacking organization will not be able to declare a new war against the former defending organization for two weeks. UI/Corporations/Wars/LandingPageWarEligibilityTooltip
549424 Enforced peace periods are created whenever wars end because of an accepted surrender offer or the destruction/removal of a war headquarters structure.

If a war ends through an accepted surrender offer, then neither the former attacking or defending organizations from that war will be able to declare new wars against their counterparts from that war for two weeks.

If a war ends through the destruction or removal of a war headquarters structure, then the former attacking organization of that war will be unable to declare new wars against the former defending organization. In this case the enforced peace is only one-way and the former defenders are free to declare new wars against the former attackers if they wish. If a war ends through the destruction or removal of a war headquarters structure, then the former attacking organization of that war will be unable to declare new wars against the former defending organization. In this case the enforced peace is only one-way and the former defenders are free to declare new wars against the former attackers if they wish.		 UI/Corporations/Wars/LandingPagePeaceTooltip

549539 This large Entropic Disintegrator is only seen in use on Triglavian battleships, these massive ships being capable of managing the considerable radiation and enormous gravitational tidal forces the weapon generates. At the energy levels of this superheavy weapon system, the tidal forces are such that special systems are built into the ship to counteract them.

Entropic Disintegrators draw on the tremendous power of the Triglavian singularity-based energy systems to convert exotic matter into a particle stream directed with locally generated entropic force. While powerful, the range of the weapon is limited by the attenuation of entropic forces, which dissipate critically beyond the optimal range. As a result this weapon has no falloff range.

The particle stream generates thermal and explosive reactions on impact, and the entropic forces resolve into a localized gravitational conduit that steadily increases the acceleration on the exotic particles. In effect, the weapon's damage potential increases to a maximum level as long as the particle stream is kept on the same target.

Requires exotic plasma charge ammo types: Baryon, Meson, and Tetryon. 549885 Using the Triglavian Vedmak-class cruiser as a basis, the designers of the Ikitursa have fashioned a powerful heavy assault cruiser from the already potent core design. The Ikitursa has been adapted for capsuleer service using systems based on the venerable Eagle-class heavy assault cruiser and has the powerful defenses and hard striking power one would expect of such a vessel wielding heavy entropic disintegrators.

As a heavy assault cruiser, the Ikitursa can use an assault damage control for enhanced defense and benefits from increased entropic disintegrator range and damage, while its Triglavian core systems give it advantages in the use of energy neutralizer and pulse weapons, as well as remote armor repairers.

"We can confirm that Ishukone's propriety Heavy Assault Cruiser Enhancement Package can be adapted for use in conversion of the Vedmak design to a heavy assault configuration. The basic technology allowing for damage resistance spiking will function on command and microwarpdrive bloom is reduced using the standard techniques. We did attempt to improve shield systems on prototype 2 but overtuning the thermo-kinetic shielding caused a singularity instability alert and the experiment was aborted. Recommend further research and experimentation in an isolated test location." – excerpt from report to Caldari Navy Design Bureau 47 from Ishukone Corporation		 Using the Triglavian <i>Vedmak</i>-class cruiser as a basis, the designers of the Ikitursa have fashioned a powerful heavy assault cruiser from the already potent core design. The Ikitursa has been adapted for capsuleer service using systems based on the venerable <i>Eagle</i>-class heavy assault cruiser and has the powerful defenses and hard striking power one would expect of such a vessel wielding heavy entropic disintegrators.

As a heavy assault cruiser, the Ikitursa can use an assault damage control for enhanced defense and benefits from increased entropic disintegrator range and damage, while its Triglavian core systems give it advantages in the use of energy neutralizer and pulse weapons, as well as remote armor repairers.

<i>"We can confirm that Ishukone's propriety Heavy Assault Cruiser Enhancement Package can be adapted for use in conversion of the Vedmak design to a heavy assault configuration. The basic technology allowing for damage resistance spiking will function on command and microwarpdrive bloom is reduced using the standard techniques. We did attempt to improve shield systems on prototype 2 but overtuning the thermo-kinetic shielding caused a singularity instability alert and the experiment was aborted. Recommend further research and experimentation in an isolated test location."</i> – excerpt from report to Caldari Navy Design Bureau 47 from Ishukone Corporation		 Item description for "Ikitursa" (typeID 52252)
549886 A modification of the Collective's Kikimora-class destroyer, the Draugur design takes the core of the Triglavian hull design and completely overhauls it to produce a potent example of the command destroyer type of vessel. The Draugur's design has taken principles and technology from the Minmatar Bifrost-class of command destroyer, while retaining the energy systems and characteristic weaponry of Triglavian ships.

As a command destroyer, the Draugur can use command bursts and micro jump field generators, while its Triglavian core systems give it advantages in the use of energy neutralizer and pulse weapons, as well as remote armor repairers.

"The Kikimora hull is entirely viable for conversion to a command destroyer pattern and we believe it will be possible to incorporate the high-capacity power couplings for a micro jump field generator without difficulty. The couplings and related warp field systems will require additional shielding from the entropic radiation of the weapon system but this is offset by existing hull integrity thresholds being well above the tolerances for jump field use." – excerpt from a proposal from Core Complexion/Thukker Mix Elgoi VIII Collaborative Design Circle		 A modification of the Collective's <i>Kikimora</i>-class destroyer, the Draugur design takes the core of the Triglavian hull design and completely overhauls it to produce a potent example of the command destroyer type of vessel. 549902 Standings are a measure of reputation, and affect your access to missions and other content. Successfully completing missions for an agent will increase your standings with:

- The agent personally
- The agent's corporation
- Their corporation's faction

Likewise, failing missions and destroying a faction's property will reduce your standings with them and their affiliates. Note: gaining standings with a faction will also improve your standings with their factional allies, while reducing standings with their enemies. So choose your allies wisely!

When deciding to offer you missions, agents will look at the highest standings you have achieved with either their corporation or faction. Higher standings will unlock higher level agents within that corporation or faction.		 Standings are a measure of reputation, and affect your access to missions and other content. 549946 In Factional Warfare you fight to gain or hold control of systems by completing sites and missions.

Each system can be in one of the following states:

- Stable
- Contested (0% to 100%)
- Vulnerable

Complexes are cosmic anomaly sites that are shown in your Probe Scanner Window.		 In Factional Warfare you fight to gain or hold control of systems by completing sites and missions.

550160 World Ark Proving Ground:

Optimal Fleet Size: 10 Pilots.

Military Intelligence:

Large electromagnetic disturbances indicate the presence of an as-yet-unseen form of Triglavian Conduit. Gravimetric and Magnetometric analysis of the area to determine threat level and composition are inconclusive at this point. We suggest that pilots form robust response fleets if they wish to engage with this "Conduit".

Background Intelligence:

Scouring the wreckage of the vessels present could yield advanced components, Triglavian data units and new Mutaplasmid types. Spectrographic readings indicate before-unseen Ores in the vicinity of the "Conduit". Attain samples of these Ores once you have secured the area.

Additionally, vector analysis of Leviathanic Fleets predict a very high chance of this "Conduit" being their ultimate destination. This class of fleet has been observed employing advanced, high-end Entropic Disintegrator variants.

550216 Planetary Production is the process of establishing colonies to extract resources from the surface of planets.

You must first establish a Command Center you are colonizing. Your colony can then be expanded with specialized structures that refine those resources into more advanced materials and byproducts.

Resources from the planetary surface can then be launched into orbit directly from the Command Center, or (for a tax) safely transferred to the nearby orbiting Planetary Customs Office (POCO).

Requirements:

- Command Center, suited to the type of planet you are colonizing.		 Planetary Production is the process of establishing colonies to extract resources from the surface of planets.

550222 Cosmic Signatures are faint signals that can be pinpointed by deploying an array of Core Scanner Probes.

- Probe Launcher
- Probes

550347 This bioadaptive mutaplasmid tool is designed to interface with and alter critical damage management systems. As such this mutaplasmid could be used to mutate the performance characteristics of most damage controls.

Triglavian bioadaptive technology makes extensive use of engineered colonies of extremophilic bacteria, that are used to grow, harvest and adapt various resources found in Abyssal Deadspace. Artificial colonizing plasmids integrated into specialist tools used for direct adaptation of technology can be found in Triglavian caches in various stages of development. These mutaplasmids can be used to alter the characteristics of a wide variety of equipment types, depending on the strain and the bioadaptive tool with which they are integrated.

The mutaplasmid colony integrated into this bioadaptive tool is highly unstable, with a high rate of reproduction and mutation. The mutational benefits of using this mutaplasmid are potentially very high but the risks are also extreme. Triglavian bioadaptive technology makes extensive use of engineered colonies of extremophilic bacteria, that are used to grow, harvest and adapt various resources found in Abyssal Deadspace. Artificial colonizing plasmids integrated into specialist tools used for direct adaptation of technology can be found in Triglavian caches in various stages of development. These mutaplasmids can be used to alter the characteristics of a wide variety of equipment types, depending on the strain and the bioadaptive tool with which they are integrated.

The mutaplasmid colony integrated into this bioadaptive tool has begun to decay and mutation effects will be less pronounced as a result. While possible mutational benefits are low, the risks of using this mutaplasmid are also reduced.		 Item description for "Unstable Assault Damage Control Mutaplasmid" (typeID 52231)
